  "prompt": "Has Voyager-1 confirmed that there are no Planet X and Nemesis star?",
  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, Voyager 1 has not specifically confirmed the existence or non-existence of hypothetical objects such as Planet X or the Nemesis star. Voyager 1 is primarily focused on exploring the outer solar system and the interstellar medium, and its data collection has provided valuable insights into the characteristics of space beyond the heliosphere.\n\nThe concept of Planet X often refers to a hypothetical large planet beyond Neptune that could explain certain gravitational effects observed in the Kuiper Belt, while Nemesis is a theoretical companion star to the Sun, proposed to explain perceived periodic extinctions on Earth. However, there has been no definitive evidence supporting the existence of either one.\n\nAstronomers continue to investigate the outer solar system and beyond, using various observational techniques and instruments. While Voyager 1 has contributed to our understanding of the heliosphere and interstellar space, it has not provided data directly confirming or disproving the existence of these hypothetical bodies.",
